-- JFK, Newark Airports Are Expected to Reopen at 6 P.M. Local Time, FAA Says
-- B y   A a r o n   C l a r k
-- 2010-12-27T19:42:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/new-york-s-kennedy-airport-expected-to-reopen-at-6-p-m-faa-website-says.html
New York’s John F. Kennedy
International Airport and New Jersey’s Newark Liberty Airport
are expected to open at 6 p.m. today, the Federal Aviation
Administration said on its  website .  New York’s LaGuardia Airport is scheduled to resume
operations at 4 p.m. after a 12-hour shutdown caused by a
snowstorm, according to the FAA. Both Kennedy and Newark closed
yesterday.  More than 6,000 flights have been canceled in the region
after snowstorms blanketed cities from New York to Boston.  To contact the reporter on this story:
